Write a program to open Opera browser 

package SeleniumAssignment;
import org.openqa.selenium.WebDriver;
import org.openqa.selenium.opera.OperaDriver;
  public class OpenBrowser {
	public static void main(String[] args) {
	  WebDriver wd = new OperaDriver();
	  wd.get("https://www.google.com/");
	  Thread.sleep(3000);
	  wd.quit();
	}
  }

What is the difference between driver.quit() and driver.close()
driver.quit:
>It close all the browser windows and end the session
>all tabs and browsers closed
>we cannot resuse a driver after using quit
driver.close:
>It close only current browser/tab window

